https://ds-wizard.org).  \nIt is designed to guide researchers and research software developers in documenting software development, sharing, maintenance, and reuse practices.\n\n⚠️ ***This project is under active development***\n\n## Feedback\n\nPlease use [GitHub Issues](https://github.com/LUMC-DCC/sciwiz-smp-km/issues) to provide feedback.  \nSee the issue templates for guided feedback.\n\n--- \n\n## License\n\nContents are licensed under the [Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC BY 4.0)](https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/).\n\n","version":"0.1.1"},{"createdAt":"2025-07-30T09:30:16.36218Z","description":"A Knowledge Model for creating Software Management Plans (SMPs) ","events":[],"forkOfPackageId":null,"id":"lumc:smp:0.1.2","kmId":"smp","license":"CC-BY 4.0 ","mergeCheckpointPackageId":null,"metamodelVersion":17,"name":"Software Management Plan","nonEditable":false,"organizationId":"lumc","phase":"ReleasedPackagePhase","previousPackageId":"lumc:smp:0.1.1","readme":"# SMP knowledge model\n\nThis is Knowledge Model for creating **Software Management Plans (SMPs)** using the [Data Stewardship Wizard (DSW)](https://ds-wizard.org).  \nIt is designed to guide researchers and research software developers in documenting software development, sharing, maintenance, and reuse practices.\n\n⚠️ ***This project is under active development***\n\n## Feedback\n\nPlease use [GitHub Issues](https://github.com/LUMC-DCC/sciwiz-smp-km/issues) to provide feedback.  \nSee the issue templates for guided feedback.\n\n--- \n\n## License\n\nContents are licensed under the [Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC BY 4.0)](https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/).\n\n","version":"0.1.2"},{"createdAt":"2025-10-02T18:11:02.310824Z","description":"A Knowledge Model for creating Software Management Plans (SMPs) ","events":[{"annotations":{"changed":false},"createdAt":"2025-10-02T11:30:57.369Z","entityUuid":"ceaad948-46e9-4248-8e66-891b905e3a8b","eventType"